<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80F51337EC1FDB03D48FC9C" pageId="15" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80F51337EC1FDB03D48FC9C" blockId="15.[151,760,612,987]" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80F51337EC1FDB03E56FD9C" bold="true" box="[151,279,612,635]" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80F51337F4DFDB03D56FD9C" authorityName="Huang, Li &amp; Yin" authorityYear="2018" box="[283,535,612,635]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraculeus">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80F51337F4DFDB03D56FD9C" box="[283,535,612,635]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Pselaphodes paraculeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80F51337F55FD503E1EFD7C" box="[259,351,644,667]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80F51337FC1FD503EB7FD7C" box="[407,502,644,667]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80F51337C31FD503DE8FD7C" box="[615,681,644,667]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">China</collectingCountry>
, and is here newly record from 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80F51337FC9FD703D68FD5C" box="[415,553,676,699]" country="Laos" name="Bolikhamxai" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Bolikhamsai</collectingRegion>
, central 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80F51337CD0FD703DFCFD5C" box="[646,701,676,699]" name="Laos" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Laos</collectingCountry>
. This species is externally similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80F51337F8AFD103F8EFD1C" authority="Yin, Li &amp; Zhao, 2010" authorityName="Yin, Li &amp; Zhao" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeus">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80F51337F8AFD103EADFD3C" box="[476,492,708,731]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80F51337FAFFD103D0BFD3C" box="[505,586,708,731]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">aculeus</emphasis>
Yin, Li &amp; Zhao, 2010
</taxonomicName>
, which is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80F51337C65FD303D37FD1C" box="[563,630,740,763]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">China</collectingCountry>
, but can be separated from the latter by the median lobe of aedeagus with a round, rather than deeply concave, apex. Compared to that from 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80F51337F71FC903EC7FCBC" box="[295,390,836,859]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, the male from 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80F51337C6DFC903D2EFCBC" box="[571,623,836,859]" name="Laos" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Laos</collectingCountry>
shows little variation in the shape of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80F51337EC1FC503FBCFC3C" pageId="15" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80F51337EC1FC503FBCFC3C" blockId="15.[151,760,612,987]" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80F51337EC1FC503E69FC7C" bold="true" box="[151,296,900,923]" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</emphasis>
China: Guangxi, Guizhou; Laos: 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80F51337CD0FC503FECFC5C" country="Laos" name="Bolikhamxai" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Bolikhamsai</collectingRegion>
(H UAN G et al. 2018; this paper). 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80F51337C47FC703FB7FC3C" bold="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">
First country record for 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80F51337EE9FC103FB7FC3C" box="[191,246,964,987]" name="Laos" pageId="15" pageNumber="50">Laos</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
